                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.7353b W 52/77: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harvey</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-03-27T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 27, 1923—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>68. Lisbon Legation reports<note n="78" xml:id="d172fn78">Telegram no. 12, Mar.
                        22, 1923; not printed.</note> that on March 21 the British Minister to
                    Portugal made a strong protest to the Prime Minister against <pb facs="0407"
                        n="283" xml:id="pg_283"/> the granting of cable concessions to the American
                    companies. Try to secure an early answer to our last note to the British
                    Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
